article.headline: Fordham 71, Rhode Island 62
article.story: KINGSTON, R.I. (AP) -- Marcus Stout had 24 points and four assists to lift Fordham to a 71-62 victory over Rhode Island in Atlantic 10 Conference action Saturday. Will Daniels had 24 points and three assists, but it wasn't enough to help Rhode Island from losing their second straight A-10 this season. Rhode Island entered the week in first place in the conference, but fell to fourth with the loss to Fordham. Rhode Island (17-12, 10-5 A-10) took its first lead of the game on the final basket of the first half, with a Lamonte Ulmer jump shot with 1:22 left, to 31-30. Fordham (15-11, 8-6 A-10) responded by scoring 41-31 in the second half. Fordham held Rhode Island's Jimmy Baron without a field goal and limited the guard to just three points, well below his season average of 15.1.
